### Register DIRECTOR Maria
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{ "email": "maria2@bright.com", "password": "password123", "displayName": "Maria" }

> {% client.global.set("mariaToken", response.body.token); %}

### Register TUTOR Tom
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{ "email": "tom@bright.com", "password": "password123", "displayName": "Tom" }

> {% client.global.set("tomToken", response.body.token); %}

### Register STUDENT Sara
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{ "email": "sara@bright.com", "password": "password123", "displayName": "Sara" }

> {% client.global.set("saraToken", response.body.token); %}

### Maria creates Academy A (becomes DIRECTOR)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/academies
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{mariaToken}}

{ "name": "Bright Minds", "slug": "bright-minds" }

> {% client.global.set("academyA", response.body.id); %}

### Maria adds Tom as TUTOR
POST http://localhost:8080/api/members
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{mariaToken}}
X-Academy-Id: {{academyA}}

{ "email": "tom@bright.com", "role": "TUTOR" }

### Maria adds Sara as STUDENT
POST http://localhost:8080/api/members
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{mariaToken}}
X-Academy-Id: {{academyA}}

{ "email": "sara@bright.com", "role": "STUDENT" }

### Maria creates Course 1
POST http://localhost:8080/api/courses
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{mariaToken}}
X-Academy-Id: {{academyA}}

{ "title": "SAT Math", "subject": "Mathematics", "term": "Fall 2026" }

> {% client.global.set("course1", response.body.id); %}

### Maria creates Course 2
POST http://localhost:8080/api/courses
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{mariaToken}}
X-Academy-Id: {{academyA}}

{ "title": "SAT Verbal", "subject": "English", "term": "Fall 2026" }

> {% client.global.set("course2", response.body.id); %}

### Maria enrolls Sara in Course 1 ONLY
POST http://localhost:8080/api/courses/{{course1}}/enrollments
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{mariaToken}}
X-Academy-Id: {{academyA}}

{ "studentEmail": "sara@bright.com" }

### Tom (staff) lists courses -> sees BOTH course1 and course2
GET http://localhost:8080/api/courses
Authorization: Bearer {{tomToken}}
X-Academy-Id: {{academyA}}

### Sara (STUDENT) lists courses -> sees ONLY course1
GET http://localhost:8080/api/courses
Authorization: Bearer {{saraToken}}
X-Academy-Id: {{academyA}}

### Sara gets course1 (enrolled) -> 200
GET http://localhost:8080/api/courses/{{course1}}
Authorization: Bearer {{saraToken}}
X-Academy-Id: {{academyA}}

### Sara gets course2 (NOT enrolled) -> 404
GET http://localhost:8080/api/courses/{{course2}}
Authorization: Bearer {{saraToken}}
X-Academy-Id: {{academyA}}

### Tom lists enrollments for course1 -> sees Sara
GET http://localhost:8080/api/courses/{{course1}}/enrollments
Authorization: Bearer {{tomToken}}
X-Academy-Id: {{academyA}}

### Sara (STUDENT) tries to enroll someone -> 403 (students can't manage)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/courses/{{course1}}/enrollments
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{saraToken}}
X-Academy-Id: {{academyA}}

{ "studentEmail": "tom@bright.com" }